nodes.bodyText:
I didn't understand about what exactly line of code you are talking about, e.g. following xml:
<struct name="DisplayCapabilities" deprecated="true" since="6.0">
        <param name="displayType" type="DisplayType" mandatory="true" deprecated="true" since="5.0">
will be represent as following java code:
@Deprecated
public class DisplayCapabilities extends RPCStruct {
    /**
     * @deprecated
     */
    @Deprecated
    public static final String KEY_DISPLAY_TYPE = "displayType";
If you're mean following:
{% if p.modifier is defined %}{{p.modifier}} {% endif %}
I guess it was added for some kind of manual customisation, and after we decide to do any manual customisation I believe it also useless.
Deleting it.

